Add 'centralPurchasingBody' to the `.roles` of the party (PROPOSAL #11)

Discard. If no `tender.participationFees` have a `.type` of 'document', then access is **assumed to be** unrestricted. (WARNING)\n\nTo provide direct access to procurement documents, add `Document` objects to the `tender.documents` array, and set their `.id` and other fields.

Discard. If any `tender.participationFees` have a `.type` of 'document', then access is restricted.\n\nTo provide the cost and terms of payment for procurement documents, use the [Participation Fees](https://github.com/open-contracting/ocds_participationFee_extension) extension, add `ParticipationFee` objects to the `tender.participationFees` array, set their `.type` to 'document', and set their `.id` and other fields.
Discard. Additional information can be obtained from the abovementioned address, unless otherwised specified.

If only the contact person is different, you can use the [Additional Contact Points](https://github.com/open-contracting/ocds_additionalContactPoints_extension) extension, get the `Organization` object for the buyer, add a `ContactPoint` object to its `.additionalContactPoints` array, and set its [fields as above](#/CONTRACTING_BODY/ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY/CONTACT_POINT).\n\nOtherwise, [add a party](../operations#add-a-party), add 'processContactPoint' to its `.roles`, and set its [fields as above](#/CONTRACTING_BODY/ADDRESS_CONTRACTING_BODY/OFFICIALNAME). (PROPOSAL #9)
Add 'electronicSubmission' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and map to `tender.submissionMethodDetails`\n\n*If 'to the following address' is selected, this results in a loss of structure.* (WARNING)
Add 'written' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and discard. Tenders or requests to participate must be submitted to the abovementioned address, unless otherwised specified.
Add 'written' to `tender.submissionMethod`, and map to `tender.submissionMethodDetails`\n\n*If 'electronically via' is checked, this results in a loss of structure.* (WARNING)

Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to 'TED_CA_TYPE', and set its `.id` and/or `.name` as follows: (PROPOSAL #10)

Get the `Organization` object for the buyer, and add a `Classification` object to its `.details.classifications` array. Set the classification's `.scheme` to ['COFOG'](https://unstats.un.org/unsd/publications/catalogue?selectID=145), and set its `.id` and `.name` as follows: (PROPOSAL #10)
Set `tender.classification.scheme` to 'CPV', take the CPV code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `tender.classification.id` (PROPOSAL #15)
For each `CODE` attribute, add a `Classification` object to the `tender.additionalClassifications` array, set `.scheme` to 'CPVS', prefix by the *Main CPV code*, and map to `.id` (PROPOSAL #16)
Discard. If `tender.lots` is set, then the contract is divided into lots.
Discard. If `tender.lots` isn't set, then the contract isn't divided into lots.
Set `tender.lotDetails.maximumLotsBidPerSupplier` to 1e9999 (which parses to infinity i.e. "all")
Map to `tender.lotDetails.awardCriteriaDetails`\n\nTo provide groups of lots, use `tender.lotGroups`
If the contract is divided into lots, add a `Lot` object to the `tender.lots` array
If the contract is divided into lots, map to the lot's `.title`
If the contract is divided into lots, map to the lot's `.id`

For each `CODE` attribute, if not already added, add a `Classification` object to the `tender.additionalClassifications` array, set `.scheme` to 'CPV', and map to `.id`. If the contract is divided into lots, add the lot's `.id` to the classification's `.relatedLots`. (PROPOSAL #18)

For each `CODE` attribute, if not already added, add a `Classification` object to the `tender.additionalClassifications` array, set `.scheme` to 'CPVS', prefix by the *Main CPV code*, and map to `.id`. If the contract is divided into lots, add the lot's `.id` to the classification's `.relatedLots`. (PROPOSAL #18)

If the contract is divided into lots, map to the lot's `.description`. Otherwise, append to `tender.description`.\n\n*If the contract isn't divided into lots, this results in a loss of structure.* (WARNING)
If the contract is divided into lots, map to the lot's `.value.amount`
If the contract is divided into lots, map to the lot's `.value.currency`
Add a `Renewals` object to the `tender.renewals` array, and set its `.id`. If the contract is divided into lots, set its `.relatedLot` to the lot's `.id`. (PROPOSAL #22)
Discard. If there is no corresponding `Renewals` object in the `tender.renewals` array, then the contract isn't subject to renewals.

Add a `Variants` object to the `tender.variants` array, and set its `.id`. If the contract is divided into lots, set its `.relatedLot` to the lot's `.id`. (PROPOSAL #17)\n\nTo provide conditions for variants, use `.description`
Discard. If there is no corresponding `Variants` object in the `tender.variants` array, then variants won't be accepted.
Add an `Options` object to the `tender.options` array, and set its `.id`. If the contract is divided into lots, set its `.relatedLot` to the lot's `.id`. (PROPOSAL #21)
Discard. If there is no corresponding `Options` object in the `tender.options` array, then there are no options.

If not already added, [add a party](../operations#add-a-party), add 'funder' to its `.roles`, and set its `.name` to 'European Union'.\n\nAdd a `Finance` object to the `planning.budget.finance` array, and set its `.financingParty.name` to 'European Union' and `.financingParty.id` to the party's `.id`. If a structured identifier is used to identify the project, map to `.id`; otherwise, set its `.id`, and map to `.title`. If the contract is divided into lots, set its `.relatedLot` to the lot's `.id`. (PROPOSAL #20)
Discard. If there's no party with the role 'funder' and the name 'European Union', then the procurement isn't related to a project and/or programme financed by European Union funds.
Append to `tender.description`\n\n*This results in a loss of structure.* (WARNING)

The standard forms express exclusion grounds and selection criteria in this section as unstructured text. In the [introductory note](https://github.com/eForms/eForms/raw/master/20180604_eForms_consultation_introduction.docx) to its [eForms consultation](https://github.com/eForms/eForms), the European Commission proposes to create an extension to eForms to implement the [European Single Procurement Document (ESPD)](http://ec.europa.eu/growth/single-market/public-procurement/e-procurement/espd/), which expresses this information as structured data, following the model of the [Core Criterion and Core Evidence Vocabulary](https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/solution/core-criterion-and-core-evidence-vocabulary). With respect to OCDS, work on this section is postponed until the extension to eForms is available.
